#. [unit_type]: id=Sailor, race=human
msgid ""
"Sailors, who began traversing the ocean when they were young, are almost as "
"much at home in water as on land. In order to make all of the swift "
"movements required of a crewman, Sailors do not wear any armor. It would "
"only weigh them down, and would probably cause them to drown in they fell in "
"the deep. Their only weapon is their light rapier, which they sling across "
"their shoulder when not using it."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Shipsmaster, race=human
msgid "Shipsmaster"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Shipsmaster, race=human
msgid ""
"The master of whatever ship they are aboard, the Shipsmaster answers only to "
"the captain of the vessel. He does not do the manual labor that most crewmen "
"do, leaving that to those working beneath him, but still refuses to wear "
"armor or wield heavy weapons, as doing so would be only an invitation for "
"the sea to drown him. His weapon is his rapier, which he wields with "
"ferocious skill."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=War Galleon, race=mechanical
msgid "War Galleon"
msgstr "Galeone da guerra"

#. [unit_type]: id=War Galleon, race=mechanical
msgid ""
"The Royal Navy of Wesnoth owns a powerful fleet of deadly war galleons. "
"Their task is to hunt down pirates - or whoever they choose to call pirates "
"- and destroy them. "
msgstr ""
"La Marina Reale di Wesnoth possiede una potente flotta di mortali galeoni da "
"guerra. Il loro compito è di intercettare i pirati -o chiunque decidano di "
"chiamare pirati- e distruggerli."

#. [unit_type]: id=Elvish Civilian, race=elf
